						               													<description>Just like their owners, cats across America are ready to leave the house and end quarantine. Protect your cats (or don't) with your arsenal of PPE. Roll the die as your cats re-explore events and destinations. Fully protect your kitties and they'll enjoy tomorrow; fall short with your protections and find yourself with a thin (and ill) litter.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Game contents: 50 state cat cards, 50 defense cards, 16 social cards, 10 event cards and one standard die.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;On your turn you'll draw a card from the deck and play it. It may be a mask or vaccine that goes into your hand for later defenses, it may be a requirement to send one of your cats to a social event in the middle of the table, or it may be a start of a social event for all cats in the middle of the table already.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;If it's a social event and you hat cats in the social space from previous draws, you'll have an opportunity to give them masks or vaccines to protect them or to play a virtual defense card to have them attend virtually and bypass the event for your cats altogether.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Once everyone has defended their cats to the best of their ability you'll roll a die and determine the threat value. Any cats appropriately protected will survive and return to your home while any cats who didn't have enough masks or weren't vaccinated for the event will be discarded.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The winner is whoever has the last cat(s) standing.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
